						<h2 class="page-heading-md font-weight-extrabold line-height-heading-1 color-spacesuit-white-important">Blue Marble: Next Generation</h2>
						<p class="p-lg margin-top-2 padding-0 margin-bottom-4 color-spacesuit-white-important">Originally released 21 years ago, The Blue Marble: Next Generation is most likely the Earth Observatory imagery you have seen the most, but you probably don't even realize it. A cloud-free, global mosaic available at up to 500m per pixel spatial resolution, the collection includes monthly snapshots with and without topographic shading and bathymetry. The collection is free and open to use so take a minute and (re)discover!</p>
									<a href="https://science.nasa.gov/earth/earth-observatory/blue-marble-next-generation/" target="_self" class="button-primary  link-external-false">
			<span class="line-height-alt-1 color-spacesuit-white-important" >
				View the collection                                    <span class="usa-sr-only"> about Blue Marble: Next Generation</span>
                			</span>
